# SPINE — text privatization for PrivHSD

SPINE rewrites English Reddit posts so that **hate-speech-classification utility
is preserved** while **authorship re-identifiability (stylometry) is reduced**.
Built for the PrivHSD challenge (Council of Europe Democracy Hackathon 2026).

The input and output are CSV files with columns `ID, Author, Text, HS`. SPINE
replaces `Text` in place, one row for one row, and preserves `ID`, `Author` and
`HS` byte-for-byte. The rewriting mechanism is **architecturally unable to see
`ID`, `Author` or `HS`** — it receives only the `Text` string.

> **Privacy claim, stated narrowly (read this).** The exponential-mechanism
> selection step satisfies **ε-differential privacy per rewritten token with
> respect to the clipped MLM logits**. Composition across tokens is sequential
> and is reported as per-token ε plus token counts. The normalisation and
> canonicalisation steps are **empirical obfuscation with no formal guarantee**.
> SPINE does **not** claim formal end-to-end, document-level DP. See
> [Privacy claim](#privacy-claim-narrow-and-exact).

## What it does, per row (the "spine")

1. **Style normalisation** (deterministic, no model): lowercase; normalise
   punctuation/whitespace/emoji; repair elongation (`sooo`→`so`); fix common
   informal spellings. Every change is logged.
2. **Salient-token identification**: mark hate-carrying tokens with an
   obfuscation-aware hate lexicon (leetspeak, spacing, repeats), and optionally
   with token saliency from a small open-weight hate classifier (config flag).
3. **Protect & canonicalise**: protected tokens are *kept* but mapped to their
   canonical surface form (de-leet, de-space, de-elongate, lowercase) — the
   classifier still sees the slur *category*; the attacker does not see *this
   writer's* idiosyncratic spelling.
4. **DP rewrite of the remainder**: for each non-protected content token, mask
   it, obtain masked-language-model logits, **clip** them to a bounded range,
   and **sample via the exponential mechanism** (softmax at ε-scaled
   temperature). This is the DP-MLM construction of Meisenbacher et al.
   ([arXiv:2407.00637](https://arxiv.org/abs/2407.00637)). The budget is uneven
   and config-driven (protected / function words / content map to ε or `skip`).
5. **Reassemble & log**: every input token is accounted for in a per-token JSONL
   log (original, action, ε spent, replacement, reason), keyed by row index,
   never by author.

## Install

Python 3.10+. CPU only — no GPU is assumed.

**Core (small, no model downloads).** Runs the full pipeline, the harness, the
whole test suite and `verify.sh` using the deterministic `hash` MLM backend and
the lexicon-proxy classifiers:

```bash
python -m venv .venv && . .venv/bin/activate    # Windows: .venv\Scripts\activate
pip install -r requirements.txt
pip install -e .
```

**Real open-weight models (the intended evaluation path).** Adds a real masked
language model for the DP rewrite and a real hate-classifier ensemble for the
harness:

```bash
pip install -r requirements-hf.txt
python scripts/setup_models.py        # one-time download (CPU wheels are fine)
python scripts/setup_lexicons.py      # download a real hate/abuse lexicon (NOT committed)
```

No hosted or closed model APIs are used anywhere. All models are small, local,
open-weight, and pinned (see `requirements*.txt`).

## Quickstart (synthetic data)

A synthetic dev set in the exact schema lives at
[`data/synthetic_dev.csv`](data/synthetic_dev.csv) (regenerate with
`python scripts/make_synthetic.py`).

```bash
# 1. privatise (deterministic core path: hash backend + test lexicon)
python -m wrapper.run --in data/synthetic_dev.csv --out out.csv \
    --mode spine --config configs/test.yaml

# 2. measure locally (utility, re-identification, trade-off estimate)
python -m harness.evaluate --original data/synthetic_dev.csv --privatized out.csv \
    --config configs/test.yaml
```

Modes: `identity` (passthrough plumbing test), `dpmlm` (plain DP-MLM baseline —
uniform budget, no protection step), `spine` (the full mechanism).

The wrapper runs the diff check automatically after writing and **fails loudly**
if any of `ID/Author/HS` changed or the row count/order drifted.

## Pointing at the real dev CSV when it arrives

The real dev set has the same schema. Use the real-model config and the real
downloaded lexicon:

```bash
pip install -r requirements-hf.txt
python scripts/setup_models.py
python scripts/setup_lexicons.py                 # or drop your own term list at data/lexicons/hate_terms.txt

python -m wrapper.run --in dev.csv --out dev_private.csv \
    --mode spine --config configs/default.yaml   # mlm.backend: hf, real lexicon

python -m harness.evaluate --original dev.csv --privatized dev_private.csv \
    --config configs/default.yaml --utility-backend hf
```

`configs/default.yaml` (real MLM) and `configs/fast.yaml` (deterministic `hash`
backend, otherwise identical) differ only in `mlm.backend`. The synthetic data's
placeholder terms live in the **test** lexicon, so pair synthetic runs with
`configs/test.yaml` and real runs with `configs/default.yaml`.

## Config & the noise dial

The privacy/utility dial is `epsilon.*` in the config — the main thing to tune
between submissions, **no code changes required**. Each token class maps to a
positive ε (spent on that class's exponential-mechanism draw) or `skip` (kept
as-is). **Lower ε = more noise = stronger per-token privacy, lower utility.**

```yaml
epsilon:
  protected: skip      # hate-carrying tokens: canonicalised, never resampled
  function_word: skip  # function/stop words: kept to preserve grammar
  content: 6.0         # the style-bearing remainder  <-- THE DIAL
  default: 6.0
mlm:
  backend: hf          # hf (real MLM) | hash (deterministic, no download)
  model: distilroberta-base
  top_k: 48            # candidate-set size for the exponential mechanism
  clip: 5.0            # logit clip magnitude C; scores live in [-C, C]
```

To privatise more aggressively, lower `epsilon.content` (e.g. `3.0`, `1.0`); to
preserve more utility, raise it. `dpmlm` mode ignores the protection step and
spends `epsilon.content` uniformly on every content/function token.

## Module map

```
src/mechanism/   the spine (receives ONLY Text; never sees other columns)
  tokenize.py      lossless word/url/mention/hashtag/sep segmentation
  normalize.py     deterministic style normalisation (idempotent, logged)
  lexicon.py       obfuscation-aware hate-term matching (leet/spacing/repeats)
  salient.py       token classification (protected/function/number/content)
  canonicalize.py  protected tokens -> canonical surface form
  mlm.py           MLM backends: HFMaskedLM (real) | HashMLM (deterministic)
  dp.py            logit clipping + exponential mechanism (the DP step)
  rng.py           per-row seed policy (see SEED_POLICY.md)
  saliency.py      optional classifier saliency (off by default, HF-gated)
  spine.py         orchestrator: privatize(text, config) -> (new_text, log)
src/wrapper/     CSV IO + CLI + the preservation diff check
src/harness/     offline measurement (the ONLY code that reads Author)
  classifiers.py   hate-classifier ensemble (hf | proxy); decoupled from mechanism
  utility.py       HS-classification F1 / agreement, original vs privatised
  reident.py       char n-gram TF-IDF + linear SVM (+ optional transformer probe)
  tradeoff.py      the LOCAL trade-off estimate
  evaluate.py      CLI
src/stretch/     scaffold: candidate-selection layer (EM selection implemented;
                 generative proposer NotImplemented by design)
```

Boundaries are enforced by tests: the mechanism imports nothing from the harness
or wrapper and never references the `Author` column; the harness imports nothing
from the mechanism.

## Privacy claim (narrow and exact)

- The **exponential-mechanism selection** of a replacement token (in
  `dp.py`) satisfies **ε-DP with respect to the clipped logit score vector**:
  scores are clipped to `[-C, C]` (so the score range / sensitivity is `Δ = 2C`)
  and candidate `i` is sampled with probability `∝ exp(ε · uᵢ / (2Δ))`. Clipping
  is always applied before the softmax.
- **Composition** across rewritten tokens is **sequential**; we report **per-token
  ε plus token counts** in the JSONL log (we do not collapse them into a single
  document-level ε).
- **Normalisation and canonicalisation** are **empirical obfuscation with no
  formal privacy guarantee**. They reduce idiosyncratic-spelling leakage but are
  not part of any ε.
- We do **not** claim formal end-to-end, document-level differential privacy.

Baseline reference: **Meisenbacher, Markus, et al., "DP-MLM"**,
[arXiv:2407.00637](https://arxiv.org/abs/2407.00637). No other claims here are
uncited.

## Evaluation honesty

The harness prints a **local trade-off estimate**

```
TO = (Utility_privatized / Utility_original) − (Privacy_privatized / Privacy_original)
```

where Utility is ensemble HS-classification macro-F1 (higher is better) and
Privacy is the re-identification attacker's top-1 accuracy (lower is better).

**This is a LOCAL APPROXIMATION of the organiser's hidden evaluator, not the
official score.** It is computed from *our own* probe models. **Do not overfit to
it.** Improving these specific probe numbers (e.g. by tuning against our SVM or
our proxy classifiers) does not guarantee improvement on the hidden evaluator and
may hurt it. Treat the estimate as a smoke signal and a relative comparison
between configs, never as a target to maximise.

## Verify

```bash
PYTHON=.venv/Scripts/python.exe bash scripts/verify.sh   # or: bash scripts/verify.sh
```

Runs the full pytest suite, all three modes end-to-end on synthetic data, the
harness on each output, and two consecutive production spine runs (Text differs,
other columns stable). Observed results are recorded in
[VERIFICATION.md](VERIFICATION.md). Runtime throughput may be printed but is not
a documented claim.

## Safety note on data

The real data contains offensive language. This repo is **public**: it commits
**no real slurs**. Test fixtures and the synthetic data use only mild insults and
made-up placeholder tokens registered in a test lexicon (`configs/test.yaml`).
Real lexicons are downloaded at setup and are git-ignored.
